                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-defend1909" type="age" value="36"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18310407-277-off1473" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-off1473" type="offenceCategory" value="sexual"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-off1473" type="offenceSubcategory" value="bigamy"></interp>
               bigamy
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-277-person1910">
                  DANIEL 
                  HONE
               <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1910" type="surname" value="HONE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1910" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1910" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Castle-street, Bloomsbury - I am a hair-dresser. I went to the parish church of St. Martin in the Fields, with the prisoner, my wife, and another person - the prisoner was there married to my sister, 
               
                  <persName id="t18310407-277-victim1912" type="victimName">
                     Elizabeth 
                     Hone
                  <interp inst="t18310407-277-victim1912" type="surname" value="Hone"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-victim1912" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-victim1912" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            ; she was at that time single - she is still alive; they lived together till last Spring - I think in April last he left her.</p>
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t18310407-277-victim1914" type="victimName">
                     SUSAN TIBBS 
                     ROWEL
                  <interp inst="t18310407-277-victim1914" type="surname" value="ROWEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-victim1914" type="given" value="SUSAN TIBBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-victim1914" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            . I live in George-street, Portman Chapel. I have known the prisoner two years last August - I understood him to be single, and that he was living in Marylebone-lane; I went to Christchurch, Spitalfields, with him on the 25th of last May - we were married there; the pew-opener and the clerk were present - I was married in the name of 
               <persName id="t18310407-277-person1915">
                  Susan 
                  Rowel
               <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1915" type="surname" value="Rowel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1915" type="given" value="Susan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1915" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; a friend of mine heard the prisoner was married, while I was in the country with him, at Overton, in Hampshire, and when I came to town, seven weeks or two months after we were married, I heard of it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I was with her drinking in Tottenham-court-road, two or three days before I was married, I got nearly tipsy, and I told her I was married. Witness. No, he did not - I never knew it; I have been with him there several times, and have taken a glass of ale, but have never been intoxicated - he never told me he was married.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I told her the very day, that I had not money to provide for the marriage, and she had better put it off to a future time. Witness. I did pay for the marriage, but I never understood he wished to put it off - I was living in Carpenter's-buildings, London-wall, in service, up to the day of the marriage.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. After we came to London she agreed to go to service; I got work at Cambridge - she heard where I was, and, as she was in the family-way, came down to me; being out of a situation I came to London, and she agreed to go to her aunt's - while she was there she was confined. Witness. I had a child on the 19th of January - I did not go to him without his sending for me.</p>

               <p>Prisoner. I lived very comfortably with my first wife, and she proved a very good one till we removed to Westminster, when she got acquainted with a man named Mettel - she used to go out with him, and get intoxicated - she came to me, and took away the money I had to provide Counsel with, and left me without; she had this 
               <persName id="t18310407-277-person1916">
                  Susan 
                  Rowel
               <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1916" type="surname" value="Rowel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1916" type="given" value="Susan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-277-person1916" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             with her at the time - she told me there<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183104070122"></xptr>would he no trial, for they would keep away; I have no witnesses on that account.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310407-277-verdict1474" type="verdictDescription">
